{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"062d45e1-9156-4c73-aaf1-844819d91ccd","content":"Here's how to migrate from `VSTest@3` to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** in Azure Pipelines:\n\n### 1. Update your `.csproj`\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis makes each test project a self-contained executable using Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\n### 2. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\n```yaml\n# Before\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testSelector: 'testAssemblies'\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n### 3. Publish TRX results & coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key notes\n\n- **`condition: always()`** ensures results publish even on test failure.\n- For Cobertura format coverage, add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet package and use `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` instead.\n- Microsoft.Testing.Platform is invoked automatically by `dotnet test` when `EnableMSTestRunner` is set — no extra tooling needed.\n- If you use `runsettings`, pass them via `arguments: '--settings my.runsettings'`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bf3184dc-8f27-4fab-b30f-4855b6c1a089","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have specific migration guidance. Let me provide general guidance based on my knowledge of the Microsoft.Testing.Platform migration from VSTest.","outputTokens":585,"requestId":"9848:1230E4:176191:1E9FD5:69FFD84B"},"id":"db428b1b-d07e-48de-8bd7-b01c609f19bb","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:59:02.570Z","parentId":"7ce0dafd-a2e1-4b05-b581-5561ff868dc0"}
